OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1774861565
OL,3,CFirst British woman to win Olympic
OL,4,Cathletics gold dies aged 86
OL,6,FThe first female British athlete to
OL,7,Fwin an Olympic gold medal in athletics
OL,8,Fhas died at the age of 86.
OL,10,FMary Rand from Somerset won the track
OL,11,Fand field Olympics gold medal in the
OL,12,Flong jump at the Tokyo Games of 1964.
OL,14,FUntil recently, she was the only
OL,15,FBritish woman to win three medals at
OL,16,Fthe same Olympics, having also won a
OL,17,Fsilver and bronze in the 1964 Games.
OL,19,FThe athlete grew up in Wells and
OL,20,Freceived an athletics scholarship from
OL,21,FMillfield School.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/4
